race.comment: Tricky race to assess with a few of these facing the starter for the first time. MONAKEED (10) is one of them but has shown ability at the trials and won't need to be a superstar to be competitive against this lot. Sure to be well-educated out of the Hoysted barn and can run a big race on debut. CLIODHNA MAEVE (8) has had a few chances but has hit the top five in nine of her past ten outings and looks to be working up to a maiden victory. Include from the favourable draw. The well-bred MAGIC SNITZEL (13) (dam was a Listed winner and G2 placed) is another on debut but hails from an astute yard and Wilson-Taylor stays on top for race day. Keep safe. ZEAMAIZE (6) makes some appeal despite the sticky barrier. While RALOS STAR (3) could be one at odds.
